# Repository Overview

This repository contains two tightly coupled parts:

1. SwiftUI iOS app in `WorkoutApp`
2. Cloudflare Worker backend in `backend/coach-worker`

The app is a personal workout tracker with:
- workout programs and workout templates
- active workout execution with set logging and supersets
- workout history and exercise analytics
- profile/statistics screens
- AI Coach
- local backup + cloud backup/sync
- async workout summary generation

## Core Architecture

- `AppStore` is the main source of truth for app data.
- Persisted app state is represented by `AppSnapshot`.
- Coach/cloud integration is centered around:
  - `CoachFeature.swift`
  - `CloudSyncStore`
  - `CoachStore`
  - `WorkoutSummaryFeature.swift`
- Cloud backend contract changes must always be reviewed on both sides:
  - iOS request/response code
  - worker schemas/routes/state logic

## Global Rules

- Prefer minimal, scoped changes over broad refactors.
- Preserve existing API contracts unless the task explicitly requires a contract change.
- Do not silently “fix” schema mismatches by dropping user data.
- Do not commit real tokens, real backend URLs, or private secrets.
- Keep changes compatible with existing persisted snapshots and backup flows.
- When touching backup, coach, or summary logic, inspect both app code and worker code before editing.
- Keep English/Russian localization intact. Reuse existing localization keys when possible.

## Before Editing

Always identify which side of the system you are changing:
- iOS-only UI/state issue
- worker/backend issue
- cross-contract issue between iOS and worker

For cross-contract issues, inspect both:
- `WorkoutApp/CoachFeature.swift`
- `WorkoutApp/Store/AppStore.swift`
- `backend/coach-worker/src/app.ts`
- `backend/coach-worker/src/schemas.ts`

## Validation Expectations

For iOS-side work:
- check compile impact
- watch Codable / snapshot compatibility
- watch `AppStore` normalization paths
- watch backup and summary flows

For worker-side work:
- run `npm run typecheck`
- run `npm test`
- keep logs useful and structured

